The paper deals with the problem of C-Planarity, which is a problem in computational geometry and graph theory. The paper presents algorithms for testing C-Planarity for embedded flat clustered graphs, which are graphs with a fixed combinatorial embedding whose clusters partition the vertex set. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely category. The paper also involves the study of embedded tree decomposition, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper uses techniques from parameterized complexity, which is covered under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also involves graph theory, which is covered under cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Finally, the paper involves the study of algorithms and complexity, which is covered under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
